# Clerk Billing (B2C)

Subscriptions and payments use **Clerk Billing** (B2C). Billing is in beta; prefer [pinning](https://clerk.com/docs/pinning.md) Clerk SDK and `clerk-js` versions. Plans and prices live in the Clerk Dashboard (not Stripe Billing products).

## Plans and features (this app)

Use these **exact** identifiers in code and Dashboard:

| Plans | Features |
|-------|----------|
| `free_user` | `3_deck_limit` |
| `pro` | `unlimited_decks`, `ai_flashcard_generation` |

Map product behavior to **features** when possible (e.g. deck limits, AI generation). Use **plans** when whole-route or whole-page access should match a tier.

## Pricing UI

- Prefer a dedicated route (e.g. `app/pricing/page.tsx`) with `<PricingTable />` from `@clerk/nextjs`.
- Use the Clerk **development gateway** for dev; a **separate** Stripe account for production (per Clerk Billing docs).

## Gating UI

- **Server Components / Server Actions**: `const { has } = await auth()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server`, then `has({ plan: 'pro' })` or `has({ feature: 'unlimited_decks' })`.
- **Client Components**: `<Show when={{ feature: 'ai_flashcard_generation' }} fallback={...}>...</Show>` from `@clerk/nextjs` (same shape for `plan`).

## Security

- **Never rely on UI-only checks** for paid behavior. Server Actions and any sensitive reads/writes must re-check entitlements with `has()` (or equivalent server-side checks) so limits cannot be bypassed.

## Examples

```tsx
// Server — feature gate
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

export default async function Page() {
  const { has } = await auth();
  if (!has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })) {
    return <p>Upgrade to use AI flashcard generation.</p>;
  }
  return <AiTool />;
}
```

```tsx
// Client — optional UI gate
import { Show } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export function ProBadge() {
  return (
    <Show when={{ plan: "pro" }} fallback={null}>
      <span>Pro</span>
    </Show>
  );
}
```

```tsx
// Pricing page (pattern)
import { PricingTable } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export default function PricingPage() {
  return (
    <div className="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4">
      <PricingTable />
    </div>
  );
}
```

For B2B/org billing, see Clerk’s B2B billing guide; this project’s entitlements above are **user** (B2C) plans and features.
